== The Kummer Map ==
One of the main tools in Kummer theory is the Kummer map. Let formula_40 be a positive integer and let formula_19 be a field, not necessarily containing the formula_40th roots of unity. Letting formula_43 denote the algebraic closure of formula_19, there is a short exact sequence

formula_45

Choosing an extension formula_33 and taking formula_47-cohomology one obtains the sequence

formula_48

By Hilbert&#x27;s Theorem 90 formula_49, and hence we get an isomorphism formula_50. This is the Kummer map. A version of this map also exists when all formula_40 are considered simultaneously. Namely, since formula_52, taking the direct limit over formula_40 yields an isomorphism

