where &quot;tors&quot; denotes the torsion subgroup of roots of unity.

== For Elliptic Curves ==
Kummer theory is often used in the context of elliptic curves. Let formula_55 be an elliptic curve. There is a short exact sequence

formula_56,

where the multiplication by formula_40 map is surjective since formula_58 is divisible. Choosing an algebraic extension formula_33 and taking cohomology, we obtain the Kummer sequence for formula_58:

