<doc id="581749" wikidata="Q1552665" url="?curid=581749" title="Chekhovo, Kaliningrad Oblast">
<text>Chekhovo (; ; ; ) is a settlement in Bagrationovsky District of Kaliningrad Oblast, Russia.

==History==
The village was founded in 1365. The name is of Old Prussian origin. The Dobrzyński Polish noble family lived in the village. In 1884, it had a population of 1,209.

